@@ -8,6 +8,16 @@ While the project is pre-1.0 (`0.x`), breaking platform changes increment the mi
 
 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Fixed
+
+- **Token refunds can no longer drive a balance negative.** A negative `credit()`
+  (refund / clawback / adjustment — e.g. the Polar refund webhook) now reclaims
+  only the tokens that still remain; the post-credit balance is floored at zero
+  across both store drivers. Previously a full refund after a user had spent
+  tokens could either 500 the refund webhook (triggering Polar retries) or
+  silently push the balance negative, after which every future charge was
+  refused. Positive credits and idempotency are unchanged.
+
 ## [0.3.0] - 2026-06-01
 
 ### Added
