+# ADR-002: Wire charity-care eligibility into the bill-diff module
+
+- Status: Accepted
+- Date: 2026-06-01
+- Mode: Team handoff (Solution Architect → Dev Clone)
+- Goal: Counterbill — ship the bill-diff module end-to-end
+- Related: ADR-003 (parser seam), ADR-004 (bill persistence) — independent, no overlap
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib/analysis/charityCare.ts` already exports a complete, tested, pure
+`estimateCharityCare({ annualIncome, householdSize, billTotal, policy? })`
+returning a `CharityCareEstimate` (FPL%, tier, discountPct, estimatedDiscount,
+estimatedRemaining, note). It is consumed by DocumentStudio / templates /
+levers — but **NOT** by the bill-diff feature.
+
+`src/features/bill-diff/components/BillDiffDashboard.tsx:64` hard-codes the copy
+"...four contested, **one charity-care reduction**" while computing nothing — no
+household/income input, no estimate, no getter. The dashboard reads all domain
+data through the single async boundary `@/lib/data` (`getCaseBill`,
+`getTranscript`, …). The canonical precedent for bridging an analysis module to
+that boundary is `src/lib/data/disputes.ts`, which wraps `overcharge.ts` behind
+async getters and re-exports through `index.ts`.
+
+The estimator exists; the gap is purely the **data-layer wiring + one render**.
+
+## Decision
+
+Bridge the existing estimator into the bill-diff feature by mirroring
+`disputes.ts`. Do **not** modify, rewrite, or re-tune `charityCare.ts`.
+
+1. Add a `CharityProfile` type (household size + annual income) to `data/types.ts`.
+2. Add a `CHARITY_PROFILE` fixture to `data/mock.ts`.
+3. New `data/charity.ts`: async `getCharityProfile()` and
+   `getCharityCareEstimate(billTotal)` that calls `estimateCharityCare`.
+4. Re-export both getters and the `CharityProfile` type from `data/index.ts`.
+5. Render one charity-care block in `BillDiffDashboard.tsx`, replacing the
+   hard-coded "one charity-care reduction" copy with the real estimate computed
+   against the post-negotiation remaining (`totalArgued`).
+
+## Consequences
+
+- The dashboard's charity-care claim becomes truthful and data-driven; the
+  estimator gains its first bill-diff consumer behind the existing async seam.
+- Profile stays a fixture (no income-input UI this run) — the swap contract in
+  `index.ts` lets a real input/persistence backend slot in later unchanged.
+
+### Explicitly OUT of scope this run (future-work, separate steps)
+- Income/household **input UI** or persistence of the profile.
+- Per-user / per-case charity profiles (fixture is global, like the bills).
+- Touching `charityCare.ts`, `disputes.ts`, `overcharge.ts`, the parser
+  (ADR-003) or persistence (ADR-004).
+- Charity-care **letter/document** generation (already lives in DocumentStudio).
+

