+# ADR-003 — Real OCR → domain `Bill` parser seam
+
+**Status:** Accepted · 2026-06-01
+**Goal:** Counterbill — ship the bill-diff module end-to-end
+**Mode:** Team handoff (scoper → Dev Clone)
+**Related:** ADR-004 (bill persistence, shipped), ADR-002 (charity-care wiring, shipped)
+
+## Context
+
+The seed step is "Replace mocked bill parser with real parse/OCR." Inspection of
+the live code shows the mock is **not** the OCR:
+
+- `src/app/api/ingest-bill/route.ts` already performs **real Gemini vision OCR**
+  (`getVisionLlm().generateImage`), returning structured
+  `{ provider, dateOfService, lineItems: ExtractedItem[] }` where
+  `ExtractedItem = { code?: string; description: string; amount: number }`
+  (route.ts:44, `coerceExtraction`). It degrades gracefully when no key is set.
+- `src/components/AnalyzeBillPanel.tsx` consumes that response into an editable grid.
+
+The actual gap: **nothing converts that extraction into the bill-diff domain
+`Bill` / `BillLineItem[]`.** The domain type (`src/lib/data/types.ts:16`) is
+`BillLineItem = { id, code, description, billed, argued, reason? }` — it needs
+stable ids, a `code` default, and an `argued` baseline, none of which the OCR
+shape carries. The dashboard (`src/features/bill-diff/.../BillDiffDashboard.tsx:36`)
+reads the hardcoded `MERCY_CASE_BILL` fixture through `getCaseBill()`
+(`src/lib/data/bills.ts:37`). There is no `parseExtractedBill` and no parser module.
+
+`src/lib/analysis/parse.ts#parseLineItems` only coerces untrusted JSON into
+`AnalyzableItem[]` (`{code?,description,amount}`) for the AI route bodies — it
+stops at the OCR shape and never reaches the `Bill` domain.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add the missing **OCR-extraction → domain `Bill`** conversion as a pure analysis
+module plus a thin data-layer getter, mirroring the existing
+`overcharge.ts` (pure) → `disputes.ts` (data boundary) precedent.
+
+- **`src/lib/analysis/billParser.ts`** (pure, deterministic, server- & client-safe):
+  `parseExtractedBill(extraction): Bill`. Deterministic ids `li-1`, `li-2`, …;
+  `code` defaults to `"—"` (matching the `BillLineItem` contract); `argued`
+  seeded equal to `billed` (no negotiation applied at parse time); `amount`
+  preserved as `billed`. No `crypto.randomUUID` here — purity is the contract.
+- **`src/lib/data/parsedBill.ts`**: `getParsedBill(extraction): Promise<Bill>`,
+  async to match the data-layer swap contract; the **only** place a non-deterministic
+  bill `id` (`crypto.randomUUID()`) is minted, at the data-layer boundary.
+- Re-export both through `src/lib/data/index.ts`.
+
+This is the literal "real parse" seam: real OCR output in → analyzable domain `Bill` out.
+
+## Consequences
+
+**In scope (this run, one task):** the pure parser, the data getter, index
+re-exports, and unit tests.
+
+**Explicitly OUT of scope this run (deferred — separate cascade steps):**
+- Rewiring `getCaseBill()` / `BillDiffDashboard` to display a parsed/uploaded bill
+  instead of the `MERCY_CASE_BILL` fixture (needs an upload→parse→render UX flow).
+- Wiring `getParsedBill` into `AnalyzeBillPanel` or `/api/ingest-bill`.
+- Persisting parsed bills via the Store seam (ADR-004) or user-scoping them.
+- Any change to the OCR route, prompt, or token economy.
+
+Trade-off: a parser nobody yet renders adds one indirection, but it is the
+correct minimal unit — it makes real extraction analyzable without entangling
+the UI rewire, keeping each cascade step independently reviewable.
+

